MemberSignature.Value: Public Property CommonEnvironmentSettings As IList(Of EnvironmentSetting)

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the list of common environment variable settings. These environment variables are set for all Tasks in the Job (including the Job Manager, Job Preparation and Job Release Tasks).
Docs.remarks: Individual Tasks can override an environment setting specified here by specifying the same setting name with a different value.

MemberSignature.Value: member this.ETag : string with get, set

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the ETag of the Job.
Docs.remarks: This is an opaque string. You can use it to detect whether the Job has changed between requests. In particular, you can be pass the ETag when updating a Job to specify that your changes should take effect only if nobody else has modified the Job in the meantime.

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the execution information for the Job.

MemberSignature.Value: member this.Id : string with get, set

Docs.summary: Gets or sets a string that uniquely identifies the Job within the Account.
Docs.remarks: The ID is case-preserving and case-insensitive (that is, you may not have two IDs within an Account that differ only by case).

Docs.summary: Gets or sets details of a Job Manager Task to be launched when the Job is started.
Gets or sets the Job Preparation Task.
Docs.remarks: The Job Preparation Task is a special Task run on each Compute Node before any other Task of the Job.

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the Job Release Task.
Docs.remarks: The Job Release Task is a special Task run at the end of the Job on each Compute Node that has run any other Task of the Job.

MemberSignature.Value: Public Property LastModified As Nullable(Of DateTime)
member this.LastModified : Nullable<DateTime> with get, set

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the last modified time of the Job.
Docs.remarks: This is the last time at which the Job level data, such as the Job state or priority, changed. It does not factor in task-level changes such as adding new Tasks or Tasks changing state.

MemberSignature.Value: Public Property Metadata As IList(Of MetadataItem)

Docs.summary: Gets or sets a list of name-value pairs associated with the Job as metadata.
Docs.remarks: The Batch service does not assign any meaning to metadata; it is solely for the use of user code.

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the network configuration for the Job.

MemberSignature.Value: Public Property OnAllTasksComplete As Nullable(Of OnAllTasksComplete)

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the action the Batch service should take when all Tasks in the Job are in the completed state.
Docs.remarks: The default is noaction. Possible values include: 'noAction', 'terminateJob'

MemberSignature.Value: Public Property OnTaskFailure As Nullable(Of OnTaskFailure)

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the action the Batch service should take when any Task in the Job fails.
Docs.remarks: A Task is considered to have failed if has a failureInfo. A failureInfo is set if the Task completes with a non-zero exit code after exhausting its retry count, or if there was an error starting the Task, for example due to a resource file download error. The default is noaction. Possible values include: 'noAction', 'performExitOptionsJobAction'

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the Pool settings associated with the Job.

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the previous state of the Job.
Docs.remarks: This property is not set if the Job is in its initial Active state. Possible values include: 'active', 'disabling', 'disabled', 'enabling', 'terminating', 'completed', 'deleting'

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the priority of the Job.
Docs.remarks: Priority values can range from -1000 to 1000, with -1000 being the lowest priority and 1000 being the highest priority. The default value is 0.

Docs.remarks: This property is populated only if the CloudJob was retrieved with an expand clause including the 'stats' attribute; otherwise it is null. The statistics may not be immediately available. The Batch service performs periodic roll-up of statistics. The typical delay is about 30 minutes.
